Other Connectivity Features: Bluetooth: This is the most common connectivity feature, allowing the smartwatch to pair with smartphones, tablets, and other Bluetooth-enabled devices. It’s used for syncing notifications, music control, and calls., NFC (Near Field Communication): NFC is used for contactless payments and quick data transfers. With this feature, you can use your smartwatch to make purchases or pair with other devices by simply tapping them together., Cellular (LTE/4G): Some smartwatches come with built-in cellular connectivity, allowing them to make calls, send messages, and use data independently of a smartphone.
